1
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:32,020
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,960
[Episode 13]

3
00:01:37,979 --> 00:01:39,240
As a native of Luodian,

4
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,039
on behalf of the folks there,

5
00:01:41,420 --> 00:01:42,360
I bow

6
00:01:43,690 --> 00:01:45,250
to Brigade Commander Zhang,

7
00:01:45,250 --> 00:01:46,060
you,

8
00:01:46,509 --> 00:01:48,280
and all the officers and men

9
00:01:48,940 --> 00:01:50,070
of the 87th Brigade.

10
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:50,740
Thank you.

11
00:01:55,060 --> 00:01:56,120
Lawyer Wu,

12
00:01:57,979 --> 00:01:58,860
I should be

13
00:01:59,729 --> 00:02:01,050
the one thanking you.

14
00:02:15,380 --> 00:02:18,070
[Xuzhou]

15
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:14,200
Kong Erbao!

16
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:17,030
I've been looking all over for you.

17
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,440
Here you are.

18
00:03:20,970 --> 00:03:23,250
I caught a wild rabbit for the buddies,

19
00:03:23,690 --> 00:03:25,220
and I saved a rabbit leg for you.

20
00:03:25,220 --> 00:03:27,620
We'll have ourselves a real treat tonight.

21
00:03:29,329 --> 00:03:31,190
You, the so-called "runaway general."

22
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:33,120
You're worth quite a bit out there.

23
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:36,130
And here you are, cooking
and feeding horses every day.

24
00:03:36,130 --> 00:03:37,810
If I sold you out,

25
00:03:37,850 --> 00:03:39,340
I might not get 1000 silver dollars,

26
00:03:39,340 --> 00:03:40,800
but I would surely get 600.

27
00:03:43,270 --> 00:03:44,460
Believe me,

28
00:03:44,829 --> 00:03:45,780
in this world,

29
00:03:45,780 --> 00:03:46,940
right now,

30
00:03:46,940 --> 00:03:48,250
aside from my family,

31
00:03:50,090 --> 00:03:51,640
no one else wants to see me.

32
00:03:52,570 --> 00:03:54,230
All my buddies died in battle.

33
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,530
They just died paving the way for others

34
00:03:56,530 --> 00:03:58,000
to get promoted and get rich.

35
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,160
They are probably drinking to celebrate.

36
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:01,830
If a stubborn bastard like me

37
00:04:01,850 --> 00:04:03,510
came back and got in their way,

38
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:04,570
Platoon Leader You,

39
00:04:04,570 --> 00:04:05,690
tell me,

40
00:04:06,530 --> 00:04:07,650
would they want to see me?

41
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:09,720
I don't care who gets in whose way.

42
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:12,430
What I'm wondering right now is,

43
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:14,220
you've been holed up

44
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:15,690
in my humble place here,

45
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,930
cooking and feeding horses every day,

46
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:19,860
and never say a word about leaving.

47
00:04:20,110 --> 00:04:21,839
What exactly are you thinking?

48
00:04:24,850 --> 00:04:27,270
Do you know the location
of the 141st Army?

49
00:04:27,330 --> 00:04:28,680
The 141st Army?

50
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:31,860
Isn't Commander Sun

51
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:33,740
your former Division Commander?

52
00:04:34,110 --> 00:04:36,240
Are you seeking justice or revenge?

53
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:38,470
To set the record straight.

54
00:04:38,470 --> 00:04:39,500
How?

55
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,409
I'm asking you.

56
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,560
How?

57
00:04:46,330 --> 00:04:48,620
I've been in the army for years.

58
00:04:48,770 --> 00:04:49,659
I know

59
00:04:49,659 --> 00:04:50,330
how things work in the army,

60
00:04:50,330 --> 00:04:51,740
inside and out.

61
00:04:51,810 --> 00:04:52,860
Tell me about it,

62
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:55,570
and I'll help you figure it out.

63
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:04,130
Brothers!

64
00:05:04,540 --> 00:05:05,660
Hurry inside

65
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:06,720
and prepare the rabbit.

66
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,620
Drop it.

67
00:05:07,650 --> 00:05:08,800
-Okay.
-Okay.

68
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,810
What's the situation?

69
00:05:13,140 --> 00:05:14,210
Tell me.

70
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:16,370
I came to Nanjing

71
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:18,300
to clear my brothers' name.

72
00:05:18,340 --> 00:05:19,890
But by some strange twist of fate,

73
00:05:19,890 --> 00:05:20,540
I was arrested

74
00:05:20,540 --> 00:05:21,810
and locked in a stable.

75
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:23,180
Before that,

76
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:25,540
Deputy Division Commander Liao Fengnian
met with me.

77
00:05:25,540 --> 00:05:26,890
He laid everything out

78
00:05:26,890 --> 00:05:28,420
to me.

79
00:05:28,450 --> 00:05:29,680
Only then did I know

80
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:31,740
why, when I asked

81
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:33,390
to go to Liu Town for backup,

82
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:34,980
my old Division Commander Sun Huaiyi

83
00:05:34,980 --> 00:05:35,860
wouldn't

84
00:05:36,020 --> 00:05:37,300
give me

85
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:38,770
a straight answer.

86
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:40,600
He just said, "If you didn't get a call,
you should go."

87
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,620
I took it as a yes

88
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:42,330
and went.

89
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:43,480
And the result?

90
00:05:43,890 --> 00:05:45,770
He said leaving the position
was desertion.

91
00:05:45,770 --> 00:05:47,180
Actually, when we arrived at Liu Town,

92
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,980
the higher-ups had already issued
a retreat order.

93
00:05:48,980 --> 00:05:50,440
We were supposed to leave.

94
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:52,540
It was just
that the telephone line was cut,

95
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:54,620
so we didn't receive the message in time.

96
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:56,480
The 6,000 brothers in our brigade

97
00:05:56,770 --> 00:05:58,010
could have retreated under orders.

98
00:05:58,010 --> 00:05:58,670
As a result,

99
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:00,520
we held Baijiazhai

100
00:06:00,570 --> 00:06:01,600
and every last one of us died.

101
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,630
And in the end,

102
00:06:02,860 --> 00:06:04,990
they were still branded as deserters.

103
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,270
Is that fair?

104
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,580
The more I hear, the angrier I get.

105
00:06:10,130 --> 00:06:11,330
What the hell is this?

106
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,760
So I have to find Lu Yun.

107
00:06:12,910 --> 00:06:13,670
Who is Lu Yun?

108
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:15,040
He's Sun Huaiyi's Division Chief of Staff.

109
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:15,770
If I find him,

110
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:16,770
I can get

111
00:06:16,770 --> 00:06:18,510
the retreat order of the 187th Division.

112
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:19,370
With it,

113
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:20,060
I can prove that

114
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:21,210
all the brothers of the 87th Brigade

115
00:06:21,210 --> 00:06:22,270
are not deserters.

116
00:06:22,330 --> 00:06:23,100
At the same time, it can prove

117
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:24,890
that the 50 of us went
to Liu Town for backup.

118
00:06:24,890 --> 00:06:25,860
You mean

119
00:06:25,890 --> 00:06:26,660
finding Lu Yun

120
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:27,860
might actually fix this?

121
00:06:27,860 --> 00:06:28,420
Yes.

122
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:30,110
What if he doesn't admit it?

123
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:32,840
He is my brother.

124
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,370
Whether he admits it or not,

125
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:35,600
I'm taking this chance.

126
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,030
Yes, you're right.

127
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:38,590
You've got to take that chance.

128
00:06:38,590 --> 00:06:39,700
My brothers

129
00:06:39,730 --> 00:06:40,390
may not be much in a fight,

130
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:42,110
but they've got ears everywhere.

131
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:44,620
I must help you with this.

132
00:06:46,460 --> 00:06:47,140
Hey,

133
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:48,370
if I help you out,

134
00:06:48,370 --> 00:06:49,690
you should do me one, too.

135
00:06:49,690 --> 00:06:50,860
What is it? Tell me.

136
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:53,380
I want you as my advisor.

137
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:55,720
What do you mean?

138
00:06:56,530 --> 00:06:58,200
Didn't I tell you before?

139
00:06:58,250 --> 00:06:59,370
A fortune teller said

140
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:00,130
I'll only stay alive

141
00:07:00,130 --> 00:07:02,040
if I stay in the army.

142
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:03,820
But I can't just sit around.

143
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:07,050
I also want to get promoted and get rich.

144
00:07:07,130 --> 00:07:08,200
I had no way before.

145
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:09,130
Now with you here,

146
00:07:09,130 --> 00:07:10,790
I've got something to lean on.

147
00:07:10,790 --> 00:07:11,990
After all,

148
00:07:12,020 --> 00:07:14,340
you're a Brigade Commander, Major General.

149
00:07:14,340 --> 00:07:15,260
Besides,

150
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:17,040
my best brothers

151
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,880
all died in Nanjing.

152
00:07:18,910 --> 00:07:20,060
Whenever I think about it,

153
00:07:20,060 --> 00:07:21,250
my heart aches.

154
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:22,330
Look at

155
00:07:22,330 --> 00:07:23,740
our 41st Army now,

156
00:07:23,890 --> 00:07:25,140
what kind of fight is this?

157
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:25,810
It's been half a year

158
00:07:25,810 --> 00:07:27,070
without any supplies.

159
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:28,660
And we were driven here by Yan Xishan.

160
00:07:28,660 --> 00:07:30,070
Is this fighting the Japanese?

161
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:31,780
This is just sending us to die.

162
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:32,970
So,

163
00:07:32,990 --> 00:07:33,950
no matter what,

164
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:35,630
you've got to help me figure this out.

165
00:07:35,630 --> 00:07:36,560
If not for anything else,

166
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:39,540
just so a few more
of our brothers might live.

167
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:42,060
Alright.

168
00:07:42,909 --> 00:07:43,710
I'll help you.

169
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,440
But if I want to leave,

170
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,720
you can't stop me.

171
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:47,580
No problem.

172
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,280
I promise.

173
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,420
Deal.

174
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:52,330
I'll get the guys on it right away

175
00:07:52,330 --> 00:07:53,659
to start asking around.

176
00:08:12,370 --> 00:08:16,130
Plain noodles!

177
00:08:24,890 --> 00:08:26,620
Newspaper!

178
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:28,610
The latest issue!

179
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,520
Newspaper!

180
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:34,900
Newspaper!

181
00:08:37,299 --> 00:08:39,080
Newspaper!

182
00:08:39,110 --> 00:08:40,950
The latest issue!

183
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:48,090
Mom,

184
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:49,250
how much more do you need?

185
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:50,250
Two scoops.

186
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:51,710
We need to save water now.

187
00:08:51,730 --> 00:08:52,660
You're cooking?

188
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:06,240
It's locked.

189
00:09:06,730 --> 00:09:08,530
Even the pipe outside is locked.

190
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:15,060
Mine is just done.

191
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:16,090
Have some here.

192
00:09:16,850 --> 00:09:17,710
No, thanks.

193
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:19,160
Thank you, Auntie Jing.

194
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:30,700
You're eating.

195
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,330
Sister-in-law.

196
00:09:35,610 --> 00:09:36,540
Sister-in-law.

197
00:09:39,490 --> 00:09:40,420
Where is the kid?

198
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:41,960
He was tired of being hungry.

199
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:44,090
He's chewing on his fingers upstairs.

200
00:09:48,290 --> 00:09:50,370
Chicken, fish, and glass noodles…

201
00:09:50,620 --> 00:09:51,830
That's quite a spread

202
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:53,680
you've got here.

203
00:09:53,870 --> 00:09:55,600
Got a pair of chopsticks for me?

204
00:09:55,780 --> 00:09:56,370
Yes.

205
00:09:56,540 --> 00:09:57,260
Yes, we do.

206
00:10:05,790 --> 00:10:06,790
Here.

207
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:15,460
Here, Sister-in-law.

208
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:18,320
Here.

209
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,090
Shuyuan, did your hand slip

210
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:33,300
while cooking?

211
00:10:36,060 --> 00:10:38,030
Your cooking

212
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:40,480
still doesn't measure up to Wanfu's.

213
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:47,210
Don't just stand there.

214
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,700
Sit down and eat together.

215
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:13,540
I remember there used

216
00:11:13,540 --> 00:11:14,180
to be a painting

217
00:11:14,180 --> 00:11:15,850
by Yun Shouping, Fish and Algae.

218
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:17,140
And in my master bedroom upstairs,

219
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:19,180
there used to be a French mantel clock.

220
00:11:19,180 --> 00:11:20,180
Where did they go?

221
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:22,190
Sister-in-law,

222
00:11:22,190 --> 00:11:24,120
I've been wanting to tell you this.

223
00:11:24,490 --> 00:11:25,450
When you bought them,

224
00:11:25,450 --> 00:11:26,980
you must have been scammed.

225
00:11:27,090 --> 00:11:27,900
Last year,

226
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,260
when I was cleaning,

227
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:30,330
an antique dealer came by.

228
00:11:30,330 --> 00:11:31,850
I packed them up and sold them off.

229
00:11:31,850 --> 00:11:33,490
He knew his stuff.

230
00:11:33,610 --> 00:11:35,020
Guess how much he paid?

231
00:11:35,610 --> 00:11:37,210
Only 20 or 30 silver dollars.

232
00:11:37,810 --> 00:11:38,570
If you want it,

233
00:11:38,570 --> 00:11:39,570
I can pay you back.

234
00:11:39,570 --> 00:11:40,020
Okay.

235
00:11:40,130 --> 00:11:40,940
Pay me.

236
00:11:46,570 --> 00:11:48,330
We're a bit tight on money lately.

237
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:49,380
Yunqi, next month,

238
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:50,420
when you get paid,

239
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:52,310
remember to give it to her.

240
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:53,900
When I get paid next month,

241
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:55,970
-I'll give it to you.
-Struggling over 20 or 30 silver dollars?

242
00:11:55,970 --> 00:11:56,970
You're not much

243
00:11:56,970 --> 00:11:58,430
of a housekeeper, are you?

244
00:11:58,780 --> 00:12:00,730
You're not much help

245
00:12:00,850 --> 00:12:01,660
around here either.

246
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:02,450
In that case,

247
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:04,390
won't trouble you two anymore.

248
00:12:04,610 --> 00:12:05,890
From next month,

249
00:12:05,970 --> 00:12:06,970
I'll collect

250
00:12:07,330 --> 00:12:08,300
the rent myself.

251
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:12,020
Well,

252
00:12:12,020 --> 00:12:13,690
it's great that you are

253
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,880
managing the house.

254
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,530
I'm just worried

255
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:17,910
people might not

256
00:12:17,970 --> 00:12:19,700
recognize you as the landlord.

257
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:21,360
Then tell me,

258
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:22,570
why on earth

259
00:12:22,570 --> 00:12:23,850
wouldn't they?

260
00:12:24,490 --> 00:12:26,340
And I'd love to hear you explain—

261
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:28,670
why they should recognize you?

262
00:12:30,610 --> 00:12:32,010
The house is mine.

263
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:32,810
Why wouldn't they

264
00:12:32,810 --> 00:12:34,050
recognize me as the landlord?

265
00:12:34,050 --> 00:12:35,160
Then call it—

266
00:12:35,180 --> 00:12:36,390
see if it answers.

267
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:38,020
Shuyuan.

268
00:12:38,020 --> 00:12:39,610
You're just being a bit childish.

269
00:12:39,610 --> 00:12:41,070
That's not how you say things.

270
00:12:41,070 --> 00:12:41,950
Childish?

271
00:12:42,780 --> 00:12:44,420
Whether it answers or not,

272
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:46,610
my lawyer will speak for me.

273
00:12:47,180 --> 00:12:48,300
Lawyer?

274
00:12:49,970 --> 00:12:50,780
Sister-in-law,

275
00:12:50,780 --> 00:12:52,780
do we really need to bring in a lawyer?

276
00:12:52,780 --> 00:12:53,570
Yes.

277
00:12:54,060 --> 00:12:55,020
Of course it is.

278
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:56,620
It's absolutely necessary.

279
00:12:59,590 --> 00:13:00,520
Sister-in-law,

280
00:13:00,940 --> 00:13:02,560
you just arrived in Shanghai.

281
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:03,890
You'd better be careful

282
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:05,280
not to get cheated.

283
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,740
We are family.

284
00:13:06,780 --> 00:13:08,330
Whatever it is,

285
00:13:08,490 --> 00:13:09,420
just come to me

286
00:13:09,610 --> 00:13:10,540
or Shuyuan,

287
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:11,920
and we can talk it over.

288
00:13:12,260 --> 00:13:14,920
Isn't there a saying
about lawyers in Shanghai?

289
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:16,670
"All proper on the surface—

290
00:13:16,970 --> 00:13:18,230
no rules underneath."

291
00:13:19,490 --> 00:13:20,060
You probably

292
00:13:20,060 --> 00:13:21,590
don't know what that means.

293
00:13:21,810 --> 00:13:23,700
Got money, got reason.

294
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,700
No money, no law.

295
00:13:25,970 --> 00:13:27,060
This is our own family's business.

296
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:28,810
If we let outsiders interfere,

297
00:13:28,970 --> 00:13:30,850
